Merge pull request #210 from Photonios/master Fixed doubling binary frames in size

Fixed doubling binary frames in size Caused by the fact that a slice was allocated for the read data (n),
and then the data was appended. However, append() does not overwrite
the contents of the slice, it makes it grow larger. Thus, the resulting
slice is n * 2.

Merge pull request #2 from ajitgeorge/fix-terminate-on-stderr-close Fix output loss when process closes before its output is fully read

Fix output loss when process closes before its output is fully read pipeStdErr signals the done channel as soon as the process closes,
resulting in the acceptWebSocket goroutine terminating even if
websocketd hasn't finished reading all of the process' stdout.

This implemenation replaces the signalling channels with input
channels.  The acceptWebSocket goroutine terminates when either input
source (process or websocket) is no longer available.
